54.6	Bay_of_Bengal	Bay of Bengal	The Bay of Bengal, the largest bay in the world, forms the northeastern part of the Indian Ocean. Roughly triangular in shape, it is bordered mostly by India and Sri Lanka to the west, Bangladesh to the north, and Burma (Myanmar) and the Andaman and Nicobar Islands to the east.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Bay_of_Bengal_map.png/240px-Bay_of_Bengal_map.png
